5.title: Leatherback Turtles in Costa Rica

episode of.title: Ocean Mysteries with Jeff Corwin (TV Series 2011– )

5.plot: Jeff travels to the Atlantic coast beaches of Costa Rica to experience an amazing spectacular event in nature which happens to be the mysterious leather back turtles securing the next generation.

6.title: Round Island

episode of.title: Ocean Mysteries with Jeff Corwin (TV Series 2011– )

6.plot: Jeff travels to Round Island in Bristol Bay, Alaska to experience walruses. He visits the Alaska SeaLife Center for a conserving mission about protecting the island sanctuary.

7.title: Best Of: Hawaii

episode of.title: Ocean Mysteries with Jeff Corwin (TV Series 2011– )

7.plot: Jeff goes on an adventure in Hawaii to explore its majestic beauty and meets some of the extraordinary animals that inhabit these islands.

8.title: Sloth Sanctuary in Costa Rica

episode of.title: Ocean Mysteries with Jeff Corwin (TV Series 2011– )

8.plot: Jeff travels to the richly diverse and beautiful rain forests of Costa Rica to explore the fascinating world of sloths which are the country's most iconic resident.

9.title: Sea Turtles in Phuket

episode of.title: Ocean Mysteries with Jeff Corwin (TV Series 2011– )

9.plot: Jeff travels to Thailand to join the efforts of a group of conservationists managing to protect sea turtles.

10.title: Giant Pacific Octopus in Prince William Sound

episode of.title: Ocean Mysteries with Jeff Corwin (TV Series 2011– )

10.plot: Jeff journeys to Prince William Sound, Alaska where he joins a team of marine biologists working to unravel the mysteries about the incredible Giant Pacific octopus.

11.title: Best of Georgia Aquarium in the Field

episode of.title: Ocean Mysteries with Jeff Corwin (TV Series 2011– )

11.plot: Jeff takes a spectacular journey around the world along with some of Georgia Aquarium's employee staff members joining a variety of critical research and conservation projects.

12.title: Costa Rican Amphibian Center

episode of.title: Ocean Mysteries with Jeff Corwin (TV Series 2011– )

12.plot: Jeff ventures into the spectacular and unique cloud forest of Costa Rica to discover some of its most endangered and fascinating residents.

13.title: Alaskan Adventure

episode of.title: Ocean Mysteries with Jeff Corwin (TV Series 2011– )

13.plot: Jeff travels to Alaska and connects with some of its iconic animals for conservation and in order to protect them from extinction.

14.title: La Tirimbina Wildlife Refuge

episode of.title: Ocean Mysteries with Jeff Corwin (TV Series 2011– )

14.plot: Jeff goes on an expedition into the magnificent rain forests of Costa Rica to experience some of the fascinating and mysterious animals that inhabit this Central American country.

15.title: Best Of: Fish Diversity

episode of.title: Ocean Mysteries with Jeff Corwin (TV Series 2011– )

15.plot: Jeff takes a journey to explore some of the wide variety and diversity of fishes in oceanic waters around the world.

16.title: Exploring the World of Venom

episode of.title: Ocean Mysteries with Jeff Corwin (TV Series 2011– )

16.plot: Jeff explores a fascinating world of venomous animals residing in the greatly diverse and beautiful Costa Rica.

17.title: Tortuguero National Park

episode of.title: Ocean Mysteries with Jeff Corwin (TV Series 2011– )

17.plot: Jeff travels to Tortuguero National Park in Costa Rica where he explores this unique and remarkably rich protected ecosystem where freshwater meets the oceanic waters.

18.title: Pinnipeds at Georgia Aquarium

episode of.title: Ocean Mysteries with Jeff Corwin (TV Series 2011– )

18.plot: Jeff takes viewers to visit some of the pinniped species that inhabit the Georgia Aquarium.

19.title: Best of Mammals

episode of.title: Ocean Mysteries with Jeff Corwin (TV Series 2011– )

19.plot: Jeff leads viewers through a journey around the world to explore the fascination and diversity about mammals.

20.title: Aquarium Partners

episode of.title: Ocean Mysteries with Jeff Corwin (TV Series 2011– )

20.plot: Jeff visits some of the most prestigious aquariums throughout North America on a mission to protect and conserve marine animals starting with Georgia Aquarium.

21.title: Ano Nuevo State Park

episode of.title: Ocean Mysteries with Jeff Corwin (TV Series 2011– )

21.plot: Jeff travels to the protected beaches of California to witness the amazing breeding grounds of elephants seals. Later, he explores the pristine coastal habitats of Ano Nuevo State Park and discovers one of the most endangered creatures in North America.

22.title: First Time for Everything

episode of.title: Ocean Mysteries with Jeff Corwin (TV Series 2011– )

22.plot: Jeff experiences a series of amazing animal encounters for the very first time.

1.title: Mysterious Manta Ray

episode of.title: Ocean Mysteries with Jeff Corwin (TV Series 2011– )

1.plot: One of the ocean's most awe-inspiring creatures is the Manta Ray but, they are stealthy creatures and not much is known about them - where they go or what they do. In this first episode of the Ocean Mysteries series, host Jeff Corwin joins Dr. Tim Mullican, the VP of Veterinary Services and Husbandry at Georgia Aquarium as he attempts to place satellite-tracking tags on 10 manta rays. Once attached to the tough Manta hide, this groundbreaking satellite technology will provide valuable data that will help Dr. Tim and other scientist's track the manta's migratory ...

2.title: Great Gators

episode of.title: Ocean Mysteries with Jeff Corwin (TV Series 2011– )

2.plot: Host Jeff Corwin ventures out to Florida's Everglades to observe the American Alligator in its natural habitat. He begins his journey at Georgia Aquarium with an examination of the albino alligators on display there. Unlike gators in the wild, albinos could not survive without human conservation. The American Alligator is an apex predator that is the designer and keeper of its environment and part of our national heritage.

3.title: Turtle Tale

episode of.title: Ocean Mysteries with Jeff Corwin (TV Series 2011– )

3.plot: This Ocean Mysteries adventure tells the story of "Murphy," an orphan loggerhead sea turtle rescued by Georgia Aquarium. Jeff takes us through his journey from rescue to rehabilitation, and finally to release back into the wild.

4.title: All's Whale That Ends Whale

episode of.title: Ocean Mysteries with Jeff Corwin (TV Series 2011– )

4.plot: Jeff Corwin dives into Georgia Aquarium's Ocean Voyager to get an up-close and personal view of the Whale Shark - the largest living fish species. Though it's name sounds scary, the whale shark is a filter feeder a fact that Jeff reveals to-side as he feeds the monsters from a rubber raft. From there Jeff travels to the Yucatan Peninsula in Mexico to track migrating sharks in the wild.

5.title: Birds of a Feather

episode of.title: Ocean Mysteries with Jeff Corwin (TV Series 2011– )

5.plot: In this episode of Ocean Mysteries with Jeff Corwin, Jeff journeys to the Breton National Wildlife Refuge in Louisiana to assist U.S. Fish & Wildlife Service and the Louisiana Department of Wildlife and Fisheries as they work to study and protect the Brown Pelican. Like the Jackass Penguin, the Brown Pelican is a precious bird that finds itself in critical condition due to catastrophic oil spills.

6.title: Reef Madness

episode of.title: Ocean Mysteries with Jeff Corwin (TV Series 2011– )

6.plot: Home to countless marine animal species and delicate ecosystems, coral reefs are critically important to our Earth's environment. On this episode of Ocean Mysteries with Jeff Corwin, Jeff dives into the warm waters off Florida's Key Largo to witness and participate in the coral reef restoration & protection efforts done by the Coral Restoration Society and Georgia Aquarium.

7.title: Best of Ocean Mysteries Part 1

episode of.title: Ocean Mysteries with Jeff Corwin (TV Series 2011– )

7.plot: From the Florida Everglades to the waters off the coast of Mexico, join host Jeff Corwin as he takes a look at some amazing moments on Ocean Mysteries. He'll come face to face with a cantankerous alligator, swim with mighty manta rays, and get up close and personal with the largest fish in the world, the whale shark.

8.title: Alien Invaders

episode of.title: Ocean Mysteries with Jeff Corwin (TV Series 2011– )

8.plot: Host Jeff Corwin teams up with NOAA, the National Oceanic and Atmospheric Administration and divers from Georgia Aquarium as they dive deep - 120 feet deep - into the stormy waters off Savannah Georgia in the effort to capture and/or eradicate lionfish - an animal with no natural predator outside the Indo-Pacific area that is it's natural home. Released into the waters off the US East Coast by unsatisfied pet owners and the destruction of an aquarium by hurricane Andrew, the unabated proliferation of lionfish threatens life on and around the local coral reefs. What's ...

9.title: Tagging Along

episode of.title: Ocean Mysteries with Jeff Corwin (TV Series 2011– )

9.plot: Even though sharks are at the top of the underwater food chain, their survival is in serious condition due to human activities. Host Jeff Corwin works alongside Georgia Aquarium experts to study sharks and their health. From tagging to drawing blood to performing an ultrasound, the team will work to better understand these apex predators and how conservation efforts can ensure their future.

10.title: Tough Jobs

episode of.title: Ocean Mysteries with Jeff Corwin (TV Series 2011– )

10.plot: Ever wondered what goes into running the largest aquarium in the world? Join host Jeff Corwin as he finds out. He suits up, and along with the experts and some powerful tools, dives into the depths of the Georgia Aquarium. He learns exactly what it takes to maintain over 10 million gallons of water and thousands of animals.

11.title: Otterly Delightful

episode of.title: Ocean Mysteries with Jeff Corwin (TV Series 2011– )

11.plot: Sea Otters are a keystone species in that they help keep their ecosystem in balance. At one point, humans hunted sea otters almost to extinction for their fur. But now, the major threats are pathogens, parasites, and oil spills. Join host Jeff Corwin as he travels to the California Coast and works with the men and women of the Monterey Bay Aquarium to learn more about sea otter pups, place them in maternal care at the aquarium, and help them develop survival skills for their eventual release. It's a monumental effort, but all worth it, to save these fascinating ...

12.title: Marine E.R.

episode of.title: Ocean Mysteries with Jeff Corwin (TV Series 2011– )

12.plot: If you think emergency rooms are just for humans, think again! Although it's on land, the Marine Mammal Center rescues and rehabilitates injured marine mammals from ailments such as diseases, entanglements, and even gunshot wounds. Join host Jeff Corwin as he goes behind the scenes in the emergency room and finds out how California Sea Lions and other marine animals are treated.

13.title: Animals in Human Care

episode of.title: Ocean Mysteries with Jeff Corwin (TV Series 2011– )

13.plot: Imagine taking care of thousands of animals, including some of the largest marine mammals on the planet. That is the monumental task that the men and women of Georgia Aquarium take on every day. Follow host Jeff Corwin as he gets a behind-the-scenes look at how these aquarists keep the animals, such as Bottlenose Dolphins and Beluga Whales, well fed, healthy, and thriving.

14.title: Stand by Your Manatee

episode of.title: Ocean Mysteries with Jeff Corwin (TV Series 2011– )

14.plot: A long time ago, sailors reported seeing mysterious creatures swimming the oceans that they believed to be mermaids. But it is now believed that what they were actually seeing were Manatees. These ethereal animals can measure up to 13 feet, have paddle-like flippers, and are extremely gentle. Join host Jeff Corwin as he explores the world of the Manatee. He'll swim alongside them, examine their unique characteristics, and endeavor to learn just how intelligent they are.

15.title: Otter the Blue

episode of.title: Ocean Mysteries with Jeff Corwin (TV Series 2011– )

15.plot: The staff at the Monterey Bay Aquarium are on the hunt for a distressed California Sea Otter that was recently released from the Sea Otter Rescue Program. Will they be able to find the otter, secure him safely, and bring him back in for treatment before it's too late? Join host Jeff Corwin as he helps locate and rescue a California Sea Otter in this exciting new adventure.

16.title: Best of Ocean Mysteries Part 2: Jeff's Favorite Ocean Memories

episode of.title: Ocean Mysteries with Jeff Corwin (TV Series 2011– )

16.plot: Over the course of the show, we've studied many amazing animals, explored incredible marine environments, and made memories we will never forget. Join host Jeff Corwin as he reflects on his favorite moments from Ocean Mysteries and looks forward to creating many more.

17.title: Circle of Life

episode of.title: Ocean Mysteries with Jeff Corwin (TV Series 2011– )

17.plot: In the hustle and bustle of our daily lives, we don't always get to see the interconnectedness of the animals that share our planet. Dive in with host Jeff Corwin as he examines the circle of life in the waters off of Monterey Bay. He'll experience the day in the life of some playful and rambunctious sea lions. And he gets up close and personal with the Ocean Sunfish, the world's heaviest bony fish and perhaps the most unique looking. He'll see how these creatures survive and play an important role in their ecosystem. It's a side of marine life you don't often get to ...

18.title: Secrets of the Deep

episode of.title: Ocean Mysteries with Jeff Corwin (TV Series 2011– )

18.plot: Beneath the surface of the ocean lies a world full of mystery. Join host Jeff Corwin as he dives into the unknown and discovers what is hidden in the depths. He'll uncover fossils from ancient creatures that reveal what life was like thousands of years ago. He'll also encounter a nighttime spectacle of manta rays and go searching for the stealthiest creatures in order to learn the secrets to their survival.

19.title: Best of Ocean Mysteries Part 3: Where Are They Now?

episode of.title: Ocean Mysteries with Jeff Corwin (TV Series 2011– )

19.plot: Throughout the course of the show, host Jeff Corwin has been a part of several amazing adventures. Some of these have included animal rescues and releases. He takes a look back at a few of these memorable stories and finds out how these remarkable animals are doing now.

20.title: Hawaiian Monk Seals

episode of.title: Ocean Mysteries with Jeff Corwin (TV Series 2011– )

20.plot: With only 1,100 left, Hawaiian monk seals are in a battle for survival. Helping them in this fight is a group of dedicated men and women from NOAA. Follow host Jeff Corwin as he teams up with them to learn more about this native Hawaiian species and how to prevent their extinction. They'll travel to a remote island to examine monk seals up close and be a part of a rescue effort to save a monk seal in trouble.

21.title: Hawaii Fly-O

episode of.title: Ocean Mysteries with Jeff Corwin (TV Series 2011– )

21.plot: The native birds of Hawaii face a harrowing future: their extinction. Large populations have vanished due to the success of invasive species. Join host Jeff Corwin as he travels to the rarely seen corners of Hawaii to get an up close look at the spectacular Laysan albatross and other native bird species. He'll learn how conservation efforts are striving to increase dwindling populations, and he'll even get a special peek at a future generation of these amazing birds.

22.title: Turtle Tale: Part 2

episode of.title: Ocean Mysteries with Jeff Corwin (TV Series 2011– )

22.plot: Once hunted for their meat and eggs, the green sea turtle's population faced extinction. But thanks to conservation efforts and public awareness, their numbers have bounced back. Travel along with host Jeff Corwin as he works with the foremost experts on green sea turtles. He'll get an up close and personal look at these resilient animals and dive into their underwater world.

23.title: Elephan-TASTIC! Seals

episode of.title: Ocean Mysteries with Jeff Corwin (TV Series 2011– )

23.plot: Every year, Ano Nuevo State Park is the mating and birthing grounds of elephant seals. Join host Jeff Corwin as he gets an amazing look at these monolithic creatures, from the 2 ½ ton males battling for dominance to the newly weaned pups learning to swim. He'll also witness how some pups are not as lucky and end up stranded or abandoned. He'll take part in a rescue and see how The Marine Mammal Center is working to rehabilitate elephant seals and give them a new chance at life. It's an awe-inspiring journey you won't want to miss.

24.title: Best of Ocean Mysteries Part 4: A Look Back

episode of.title: Ocean Mysteries with Jeff Corwin (TV Series 2011– )

24.plot: Throughout the course of Ocean Mysteries, host Jeff Corwin has been a part of several memorable adventures. In this special episode, Jeff looks back at some of these amazing moments. From a monk seal in need of rescue to swimming alongside giant manta rays at night, it's an adventure you won't soon forget.

25.title: Dolphin Tales: Part 1

episode of.title: Ocean Mysteries with Jeff Corwin (TV Series 2011– )

25.plot: This episode is part one of a special presentation of Ocean Mysteries. The story of the making of AT&T Dolphin Tales at Georgia Aquarium. Each week on Ocean Mysteries, we introduce you to some of the most compelling animals on Earth like whale sharks, sea otters, manta rays and beluga whales, all of whom have a home at Georgia Aquarium. But while the team at the Aquarium loves and cares deeply for all of our animals, they know there is something about Bottlenose dolphins which captures the imagination, minds and hearts of people all over the world. That's why Georgia ...

26.title: Dolphin Tales: Part 2

episode of.title: Ocean Mysteries with Jeff Corwin (TV Series 2011– )

26.plot: This episode is part two of a special presentation of Ocean Mysteries. The story of the making of AT&T Dolphin Tales at Georgia Aquarium. Each week on Ocean Mysteries, we introduce you to some of the most compelling animals on Earth like whale sharks, sea otters, manta rays and beluga whales, all of whom have a home at Georgia Aquarium. But while the team at the Aquarium loves and cares deeply for all of our animals, they know there is something about Bottlenose dolphins which captures the imagination, minds and hearts of people all over the world. That's why Georgia ...

1.title: The Dolphins of Indian River Lagoon

episode of.title: Ocean Mysteries with Jeff Corwin (TV Series 2011– )

1.plot: Host Jeff Corwin joins scientists and volunteers from Harbor Branch at Florida Atlantic University's Health and Environmental Risk Assessment team to study Atlantic Bottlenose dolphin health in Florida's Indian River Lagoon and uncover why these animals are the sentinels for the entire ecosystem. Jeff helps researchers carefully locate and lift dolphins out of the water and on to a research boat for observation and assessment.

2.title: Seals of Approval

episode of.title: Ocean Mysteries with Jeff Corwin (TV Series 2011– )

2.plot: Host Jeff Corwin explores Aialik Glacier and visits the Alaska SeaLife Center where he meets an orphaned harbor seal named Ali. Jeff helps the ASLC staff nurse Ali back to health and prepare for Ali's release back to the wild. Along the way, Jeff learns about other seals at the facility, including one named Atty who is pregnant with her second pup.

3.title: Steller Sea Lions

episode of.title: Ocean Mysteries with Jeff Corwin (TV Series 2011– )

3.plot: Host Jeff Corwin teams up with the Alaska SeaLife Center to uncover the reasons behind the decline of some Steller sea lion populations. Jeff travels to remote Grotto Island to witness sea lions in their natural habitat. Jeff also meets a two thousand pound sea lion named Woody and learns about the breeding program at the ASLC.

4.title: To the Ocean and Back

episode of.title: Ocean Mysteries with Jeff Corwin (TV Series 2011– )

4.plot: Host Jeff Corwin explores the incredible life cycle of Alaskan salmon and joins the conservation teams working to protect this amazing species. From collecting salmon eggs, watching them grow, releasing them into streams, and following them to the ocean, Jeff is there - every step of the way. Finally Jeff travels back to Alaska three months later to witness adult salmon returning upstream from the ocean to spawn, as the great cycle begins again.

5.title: Saving Sea Lions

episode of.title: Ocean Mysteries with Jeff Corwin (TV Series 2011– )

5.plot: Host Jeff Corwin travels aboard a research boat off the coast of Alaska for a three-day adventure with Steller sea lions. Despite continued protection and conservation, the populations of western Steller sea lions are not improving - and Jeff and the research team from the Alaksa SeaLife Center want to find out why. Jeff dives with scientists to locate sea lions and bring them on to a research boat to assess their health and track their behavior.

6.title: Best of: Wonders Beneath the Waves

episode of.title: Ocean Mysteries with Jeff Corwin (TV Series 2011– )

6.plot: Host Jeff Corwin remembers some of his most exciting deep-water dives from the series, including hunting for Lionfish, visiting an underwater coral garden, exploring an ancient deep-water archaeological dig, and experiencing the thrill of a nighttime swim with manta rays.

7.title: The Great Return

episode of.title: Ocean Mysteries with Jeff Corwin (TV Series 2011– )

7.plot: Host Jeff Corwin travels to Kodiak Island off the coast of Alaska to witness millions of salmon returning back to the freshwater streams where they were born. Jeff participates in cutting-edge field research on adult salmon and helps scientists as they study the links between salmon and their environment. Jeff also travels into the Alaskan wilderness to explore salmon as a vital food source for Kodiak bears, bald eagles, and people too.

8.title: A Bird's Eye View of Alaska

episode of.title: Ocean Mysteries with Jeff Corwin (TV Series 2011– )

8.plot: Host Jeff Corwin explores the world of Alaskan birds and their unique relationship to the ocean. Jeff visits the Alaska Raptor Center where a bald eagle named Tahoe is ready to be released back to the wild. Jeff also travels to remote Grotto Island for fieldwork with wild birds, and he visits the Alaska SeaLife Center's bird habitat to meet baby puffin chicks.

9.title: Eye of the Sand Tiger

episode of.title: Ocean Mysteries with Jeff Corwin (TV Series 2011– )

9.plot: Host Jeff Corwin joins scientists for a rare and up-close look at Sand Tiger sharks off the coast of New England. Jeff helps to carefully capture these fierce fish and bring them onto the research boat for observation, assessment, and release. Jeff also swims along-side large sharks in the world's largest aquarium in Atlanta Georgia.

10.title: Best of: Adventure Alaska

episode of.title: Ocean Mysteries with Jeff Corwin (TV Series 2011– )

10.plot: Host Jeff Corwin shares some of his most exciting experiences in the great state of Alaska including diving with Stellar Sea Lions, tracking Brown Bears on Kodiak Island, caring for adorable Harbor Seals, and exploring Alaska's vast coastline.

11.title: Gone Fishin'

episode of.title: Ocean Mysteries with Jeff Corwin (TV Series 2011– )

11.plot: Host Jeff Corwin teams up with scientists and his daughter Maya to explore the ancient world of Sturgeon and the efforts to conserve this important species. Jeff also explores the many varieties of fish around his home in New England from trout to Blue-fin tuna.

12.title: Beluga Tales

episode of.title: Ocean Mysteries with Jeff Corwin (TV Series 2011– )

12.plot: Host Jeff Corwin travels to the Saint Lawrence River in Quebec, Canada to unlock the secrets of Beluga whales. Jeff locates wild Belugas by helicopter and helps scientists identify individual whales for study. Jeff also explores the Beluga whales at Georgia Aquarium and works with the veterinary team who cares for them.

13.title: Bear Neccessities

episode of.title: Ocean Mysteries with Jeff Corwin (TV Series 2011– )

13.plot: Host Jeff Corwin travels to the remote island of Kodiak for an adventure with Alaskan Brown Bears. Jeff teams up with biologists to tranquilize and study these massive carnivores. Along the way, Jeff finds a mother bear and her two cubs in a struggle to find food. Jeff returns to Kodiak Island months later in hopes to relocate this bear family and ensure their survival.

14.title: Bringing Up Babies

episode of.title: Ocean Mysteries with Jeff Corwin (TV Series 2011– )

14.plot: Host Jeff Corwin gets an up-close look at many amazing youngsters who grow up living in or near the ocean. Jeff travels to Alaska for to see a baby walrus, stops by Chicago's famous Shedd Aquarium for a rare look at a baby Beluga whale and baby dolphin, and even helps welcome baby penguins in to the world at Georgia Aquarium.

15.title: Thar' She Blows

episode of.title: Ocean Mysteries with Jeff Corwin (TV Series 2011– )

15.plot: Host Jeff Corwin travels to the remote coastlines of Alaska for a once in a lifetime adventure with Humpback whales. Jeff teams up with scientists who study whale behavior and work to understand the fascinating feeding habits of these massive mammals. Jeff also unlocks the secrets of whale communication by recording whale songs with the latest technology

16.title: Best of: Jeff's Favorite Moments

episode of.title: Ocean Mysteries with Jeff Corwin (TV Series 2011– )

16.plot: Host Jeff Corwin relives some of his favorite animal moments from the show including an adventure with mighty Humpback Whales, Kodiak Bears, an adorable baby Dolphin, and ancient New England Sturgeon. Jeff's daughter Maya is along for the ride on this trip down memory lane.

17.title: Manatees of the Caribbean

episode of.title: Ocean Mysteries with Jeff Corwin (TV Series 2011– )

17.plot: Host Jeff Corwin travels to Puerto Rico to explore the mysterious world of Manatees. Jeff teams up with the local Manatee Conservation Center working to rehabilitate injured and orphaned Manatees. Later, Jeff explores the main breeding grounds for Manatees in the Caribbean and releases a newly recovered Manatee back into the wild.

18.title: Be Careful What You Fish For

episode of.title: Ocean Mysteries with Jeff Corwin (TV Series 2011– )

18.plot: Host Jeff Corwin boards a fishing boat on the hunt for Alaskan Salmon. Jeff works with the crew to haul in the massive catch while learning about sustainable fishing and wildlife management. Jeff also travels to coast of New England where biologists are racing to manage the Blue Fin Tuna populations of the Atlantic Ocean.

19.title: Penguins Down Under

episode of.title: Ocean Mysteries with Jeff Corwin (TV Series 2011– )

19.plot: Host Jeff Corwin travels to the island nation of New Zealand for an up-close look at Yellow-Eyed Penguins. Jeff braves the steep cliffs of the Otago Peninsula to help biologists fighting to protect young penguin chicks. Jeff also travels to New Zealand's famous "Penguin Place": a sanctuary and rehabilitation center for penguins throughout the island.

20.title: New Zealand Island Adventure

episode of.title: Ocean Mysteries with Jeff Corwin (TV Series 2011– )

20.plot: Host Jeff Corwin explores the remote island chain of southern New Zealand and encounters a new adventure on every shore. Jeff uncovers penguin nests in the forests of Bravo Island, baby sea lions along the beaches of Stewart Island, beautiful birds on Tommy Island, and helps scientists fighting to protect these natural wonders from invasive species and predators.

21.title: New Sealand

episode of.title: Ocean Mysteries with Jeff Corwin (TV Series 2011– )

21.plot: Host Jeff Corwin travels to the island nation of New Zealand for an adventure with the furry seals from down under. Jeff joins a research team racing to protect Fur Seal pups from habitat loss, explores the large Fur Seal Colony off the shores of Kaikoura, and dives with Fur Seals in the crystal clear waters of Milford Sound.

22.title: Queenstown

episode of.title: Ocean Mysteries with Jeff Corwin (TV Series 2011– )

22.plot: Host Jeff Corwin travels to the island nation of New Zealand to explore the famous region of Queenstown and work to save some the country's most endangered species. The iconic Kiwis and Long-tailed Bats are facing an uncertain future, and Jeff is on a mission to fight invasive predators and protect New Zealand's wildlife heritage.

23.title: The Living Fossil

episode of.title: Ocean Mysteries with Jeff Corwin (TV Series 2011– )

23.plot: Host Jeff Corwin travels to the protected island of Matiu/Somes off the coast of New Zealand to find a prehistoric species that walked the earth with dinosaurs. Jeff is on a mission to help rebuild an ancient ecosystem, come face to face with some of the planet's most unique creatures, and uncover secrets 200 million years in the making.

24.title: Journey with Gentle Giants

episode of.title: Ocean Mysteries with Jeff Corwin (TV Series 2011– )

24.plot: In this special episode of Ocean Mysteries, Host Jeff Corwin dives alongside brave men and women of our armed forces who were injured in the line of duty. As these wounded veterans experience the wonder of Georgia Aquarium and swim along side giant Whale Sharks, they also find the strength to heal. Jeff makes new friends, listens to heroic stories, and reminds us all to never forget the people who keep our country safe.

25.title: Best of: Adventure New Zealand

episode of.title: Ocean Mysteries with Jeff Corwin (TV Series 2011– )

25.plot: Host Jeff Corwin relives some of his favorite moments from New Zealand including the endangered Yellow-eyed Penguins of Otago, the adorable Fur Seal pups of Kaikoura, the mysterious Long-tailed Bats of Te Anau, and the breath-taking beauty of the New Zealand islands.

26.title: Healthy Habits

episode of.title: Ocean Mysteries with Jeff Corwin (TV Series 2011– )

26.plot: Jeff joins the hard working biologists of Georgia Aquarium as they care for the animals living in the world's largest aquarium. He helps deliver a stingray to his new home and works with veterinarians caring for exotic species in the aquarium.

1.title: California Sea Lions

episode of.title: Ocean Mysteries with Jeff Corwin (TV Series 2011– )

1.plot: Jeff travels to Laguna Beach, California to uncover the secrets behind a marine mammal disaster.

2.title: Animal Families of New Zealand

episode of.title: Ocean Mysteries with Jeff Corwin (TV Series 2011– )

2.plot: Jeff travels to the far side of the globe to witness the amazing families of New Zealand such as sea lions, Takhae Birds, and a colony of baby blue-eyed penguins. Their dedicated parents that help them grow for wildlife survival.

3.title: New England Animal Adventures

episode of.title: Ocean Mysteries with Jeff Corwin (TV Series 2011– )

3.plot: Jeff experiences an exploration of his native New England coastline and some of the amazing animals that make this region so special.

4.title: Best Of: Adventures at the Aquarium

episode of.title: Ocean Mysteries with Jeff Corwin (TV Series 2011– )

4.plot: Jeff relives some of his favorite spectacular moments at the Georgia Aquarium.

5.title: Zealandia: The Garden of Tane

In Hawaii, Jeff learns about the heroic efforts to save a community of albatross from predators, and in New Zealand, he explores the world of little blue penguins that build their nests on the ocean cliffs.

episode of.title: Ocean Mysteries with Jeff Corwin (TV Series 2011– )

16.plot: Host Jeff Corwin is on an epic journey from Australia to Hawaii exploring the mysterious world of sharks! Jeff works alongside expert biologists to unlock the secrets of deep-water sixgill sharks, massive sand tiger sharks, powerful bull sharks, and so much more!

22.title: Thailand Sea Turtles

episode of.title: Ocean Mysteries with Jeff Corwin (TV Series 2011– )

22.plot: Jeff travels to the beautiful country of Thailand to help save endangered sea turtles. He helps feed orphaned baby turtles, preforms critical exams on one of the rarest turtle species on earth by working alongside expert biologists.

imdb.plot outline: Georgia Aquarium is one of the world's most magical aquariums, featuring the largest single aquarium habitat in the world and more aquatic life than any other aquarium in North America. Jeff Corwin, supported by a team of Georgia Aquarium biologists, veterinarians, and subject matter experts, will travel around the world taking viewers below the surface to explore the Earth's least understood resource, our oceans and waterways, and the animals which call them home. Corwin will reveal countless animals that inhabit fresh and salt water environments, allowing viewers to connect with aquatic animals and to learn how important they are to all life on our planet.
